The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, Aug. 16: Coal India has got approval from the coal ministry to reduce the face value of its shares to Rs 10 from Rs 1,000, a move that would increase the number of the companys shares to 631.6 crore. At present, the face value of one Coal India share stands at Rs 1,000 and the company has 6.316 crore shares, chairman P.S. Bhattacharyya said.                             
	 New Delhi, Aug. 16: The road transport and highways ministry is set to award 58 projects worth Rs 19,000 crore for building over 7,000 km roads in various states. The projects relate to converting existing roads into two-lanes in Karnataka, Uttar Pradesh, Chhattisgarh, Madhya Pradesh, Orissa, Kerala, Rajasthan, Uttarakhand, Tamil Nadu, Andhra Pradesh, Bihar and Himachal Pradesh.                            
	 New Delhi, Aug. 16: Tata Steel is scouting for iron ore and coking coal mines worldwide and is in talks with two mining firms in Vietnam and South Africa for joint ventures. The company is aiming raw material security primarily for its global operations.                             
	 Mumbai, Aug. 16: State-owned Corporation Bank will offer income tax returns filing facility through its 1,000-plus strong ATM network spread across the country, the banks chairman and managing director J.M. Garg said.                             
	 New Delhi, Aug. 16: The department of telecom will not have to wait for the defence ministry to release frequencies for auctioning 3G spectrum as it has an adequate amount to give the initial 5Mhz of radiowaves to at least three players in a circle.                             
	 New Delhi, Aug. 16: The government has fixed a price of Rs 36 a share for allotment in the initial public offer of NHPC, thus raising Rs 6,048 crore, of which one-third will go to the Centre as divestment proceeds and the rest will remain with the hydropower utility PSU.                            
	 New Delhi, Aug. 16: Malaysia Airlines is offering up to 47 per cent discount on tickets from India to Malaysia. The travellers can avail themselves of the scheme from August 16 to August 30 under the Malaysia Airlines Travel Fair programme.                                                                                                                           
